content:
If your goal is to understand vast amounts of business data, and to communicate that understanding with coworkers, partners, and customers, being able to visualize your data is critical. CRM Analytics provides a chart for every need.

Customize Charts with Chart Properties
To create the best visualizations for presenting your data, use chart properties to configure Analytics charts.
Bar Charts: Use a bar or column chart to provide a quick visual comparison of related values. Use a stacked bar or stacked column chart to show groups within each bar.
Calendar Heat Map Charts: Visualize recurring discrete activities over long periods of time.
Column Charts: Show relative counts of things, such as leads or dollars. Use a stacked column chart to show groups within each bar.
Combo Charts: Display at least two related series of data, such as discrete grouped values as vertical bars overlaid with a line chart representing an average value.
Donut Charts: Show the proportion of a single value for each group member against the total and the total amount itself.
Dot Plot Charts: Use size and coloring of bubbles to display multiple dimensions and measures.
Funnel Charts: Visualize sequential data that can be broken up into stages, such as a sales cycle.
Gauge Charts: Track progress along a single measure, such as how much revenue has been realized versus the target.

CRM Analytics charts are integrated with the CRM Analytics tools you already use to explore data. Start with a dataset, explore with a lens, clip it to dashboard designer, and create a stunning dashboard.

title: Data Visualization with CRM Analytics
